            Migration from Azure to AWS
	Go to EC2.
•	Create a security group with Http and Https.
	Open AWS Application migration service.
	Go to Replication Template.
•	Select the staging area subnet.
•	Select the replication server instance type.
•	Select the EBS vol type.
•	Enable EBS encryption(if needed).
•	Select the security group you have created.
•	Create the replication template.
	Go to launch template.
•	Unselect the instance type right-sizing option.
•	Select the target subnet.
•	Select the security group.
•	Select the instance type.
•	Select the EBS vol type.
•	Create the launch template.
	Go to source server
•	Add server.
•	Select OS.
•	Select replication reference 
	Replicate all disk
	Choose which disk to replicate
•	Go to IAM section
	Create an IAM user with AWSApplicationmigrationFullAccess.
	Create user
	Go inside the user
	Go to security credentials
	Go to create access keys in access keys section
	Download the access keys file
	Paste the access keys on the required sections
•	Connect to the server which you want to migrate.
•	Download the installer through this command ~
“sudo wget -O ./aws-replication-installer-init https://aws-application-migration-service-ap-south-1.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/latest/linux/aws-replication-installer-init”
•	Run this command as well ~
“sudo chmod +x aws-replication-installer-init; sudo ./aws-replication-installer-init --region ap-south-1”
	After this you’ll able to see that your server will be created automatically.
	“AWS Application Migration Replication server” will be created in the instance section of EC2
	After replication select the source server and click on “Test and cutover”
	And launch the instance





